NEWS for Potext 0.2.0
Chris Ahlstrom
2024-03-19 to 2024-04-14

# Changelog

## [0.2.0] - 2024-04-14

### Added

- Added the moparser class for creating dictionaries from .mo files.
  It also scans the .mo file for character-set and plural-forms.
- Added an extractor class to help with the parsing of this binary data.
- Added pomoparserbase class to serve as an abstract base class for
  poparser and moparser.
- Added storage of msgid\_plural to use in reconstituting a translation file.
- Added support for nplurals=3 found in colord.mo (es domain).
- Added the ability to dump a dictionary's translations in the format of
  a .po file.

### Fixed

- Errors in character-set handling.
- Errors in plural forms handling, plus some efficiency work.
- Fixed the mini-test tar-ball.
- Many other fixes, an embarrassing number.

### Changed

- Moved some poparser code to the new pomoparser base class.
- Update the PDF documentation to match new developments.
- Support for wide-strings now universal, not just Windows, more testing is
  needed.
- Changed the dictionary maps from unordered to ordered, for better output
  of dictionary entries.

### Removed

- Minor cleanup.

## [0.1.0] - 2024-03-19

### Added

- This is the first release of the Potext library. See the README for
  more information.

### Fixed

- See the README.

### Changed

- See the README.

### Removed

- See the README.

